\f0\b \cf2 GLOUCESTER\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 Sweet prince, the untainted virtue of your years\
Hath not yet dived into the world's deceit\
Nor more can you distinguish of a man\
Than of his outward show; which, God he knows,\
Seldom or never jumpeth with the heart.\
Those uncles which you want were dangerous;\
Your grace attended to their sugar'd words,\
But look'd not on the poison of their hearts :\
God keep you from them, and from such false friends!\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 PRINCE EDWARD\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 God keep me from false friends! but they were none.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 GLOUCESTER\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 My lord, the mayor of London comes to greet you.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 LORD MAYOR\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 God bless your grace with health and happy days!\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 PRINCE EDWARD\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 I thank you, good my lord; and thank you all.\
I thought my mother, and my brother York,\
Would long ere this have met us on the way\
Fie, what a slug is Hastings, that he comes not\
To tell us whether they will come or no!\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 BUCKINGHAM\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 And, in good time, here comes the sweating lord.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 PRINCE EDWARD\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 Welcome, my lord: what, will our mother come?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 HASTINGS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 On what occasion, God he knows, not I,\
